dockerFIle- if we want to create custom image we use docker file
docker-compose- if image is already exist we just need to pull it by providing image name and version and additional configuration

docker-compose.yml -what common details need to provide

version: '3.8'  # Specify the version of Docker Compose
service:
        name: elasticsearch
        image: elasticsearch:7.10.1  # Specify the image and version
        container_name: elasticsearch_container  # Optional: Name of the container
        build:
                context: .  # Specify the build context
                dockerfile: Dockerfile  # Specify the Dockerfile name if not default
        environments:
                - discovery.type=single-node  # Set environment variables
                - ES_JAVA_OPTS=-Xms512m -Xmx512m  # Set Java options
        ports:
                - "9200:9200"  # Map host port to container port
                - "9300:9300"
        network:
                elk
